# Memory Bank (Project Truths)

## Context
- **MVP**: Interactive code assistant for the Doom codebase (expandable later)
- **Constraints**: $0 monthly, optimize for lowest cost, US-only if it affects anything, small team, 2-day MVP
- **Default UX**: Interactive answers; "take your time" enables slower/deeper mode

## Architecture
- **Pipeline**: ingest → chunk/code-aware parse → embed → index → retrieve → answer w/ citations
- **Retrieval**: Hybrid (lexical + vector) if available; otherwise vector + lightweight keyword fallback
- **Grounding**: All answers must be grounded in repo content; cite file paths + line ranges
- **Edits**: Diff suggestions preferred over paste huge files

## Indexing Scope
- **Source**: Doom (C + asm), static codebase snapshot
- **Ingest**: ~500 files/day, incremental updates supported
- **Chunking**: Code-aware (functions/structs), preserve includes/macros context

## Quality Bar
- Never hallucinate APIs/types/behavior; if unsure, say what's missing and where to look
- Any claim about code must point to at least one snippet in the repo
- Prefer minimal, reversible changes (small diffs)
